               <p>THOMAS McGILLIVRAY. I am a <rs id="t18340904-230-viclabel1293" type="occupation">surgeon in the East India Company's service</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-230-victim1360 t18340904-230-viclabel1293"></join> - the prisoner was in my employ for some time, to go out with a variety of curiosities which I brought from India from time to time, to dispose of them - I paid him for his trouble - I gave him a gun to dispose of - he returned and said he only got 4l. 10s. for it, and he had got 6l. for it - he was to sell it for me, and bring back whatever he got for it - I told him that I had discovered he had sold it in St. James's-street, instead of Piccadilly as he had told me, and for 6l. instead of 4l. 10s. - he said he sold it first for 4l. 10s. in Piccadilly, and went and purchased it again, and sold it for 6l. - the money was never in my possession.</p>
